revision.text: Possibly: A treatise on the conic sections. In five books. Book I. On the General Properties which are common to them all. Book II. On the Properties which are common to two Sections. Book III. On the Properties which are peculiar to each Section. Book IV. On the Problems relating to the Conic Sections. Book V. On the Loci of the Conic Sections, or those Problems of which the conic Sections are the Loci. By G. Walker, F.R.S. of Nottingham. (London : Printed for Charles Dilly, in the Poultry, 1794). http://library.st-andrews.ac.uk/record=b2498974~S1
